{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareCommandConfig\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">declareCommandConfig</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`declare_core_config_elab f struct binders* [where ...]` defines a configuration elaborator\n```lean\nf binders* (cfg : Syntax) (init : struct := {}) (logExceptions : Bool := true) : CommandElabM struct\n```\nthat evaluates the `cfg` configuration items to update `init`.\nAcceptable configuration syntax is documented in `Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.foldConfigM`,\nwhich includes anything that looks like `Lean.Parser.Term.optConfig`, possibly wrapped\nin null nodes.\n\nThe command will transitively derive any necessary `ConfigEval.EvalTerm`/`ConfigEval.EvalExpr`\ninstances to support evaluation of configuration options for structure fields.\nThese instances will be `private local`.\n\nSee `ConfigEval.defEvalConfigItemCmd` for further documentation.\n\nSee also `declare_core_config_elab`, `declare_term_config_elab`, and `declare_config_elab`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareCommandConfig","kind":"def","line":164,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareCommandConfig","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L164-L183"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareTacticConfig\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">declareTacticConfig</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`declare_config_elab f struct binders* [where ...]` defines a configuration elaborator\n```lean\nf binders* (cfg : Syntax) (init : struct := {}) (logExceptions : Bool := true) : TacticM struct\n```\nthat evaluates the `cfg` configuration items to update `init`.\nAcceptable configuration syntax is documented in `Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.foldConfigM`,\nwhich includes anything that looks like `Lean.Parser.Term.optConfig`, possibly wrapped\nin null nodes.\n\nWhen `logExceptions` is true, it uses the current `recover` state to decide whether or not to\nrecover by logging errors and skipping invalid options.\n\nThe command will transitively derive any necessary `ConfigEval.EvalTerm`/`ConfigEval.EvalExpr`\ninstances to support evaluation of configuration options for structure fields.\nThese instances will be `private local`.\n\nSee `ConfigEval.defEvalConfigItemCmd` for further documentation.\n\nSee also `declare_core_config_elab`, `declare_term_config_elab`, and `declare_command_config_elab`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareTacticConfig","kind":"def","line":140,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareTacticConfig","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L140-L162"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareTermConfigElab\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">declareTermConfigElab</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`declare_term_config_elab f struct binders* [where ...]` defines a configuration elaborator\n```lean\nf binders* (cfg : Syntax) (init : struct := {}) (logExceptions : Bool := true) : TermElabM struct\n```\nthat evaluates the `cfg` configuration items to update `init`.\nAcceptable configuration syntax is documented in `Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.foldConfigM`,\nwhich includes anything that looks like `Lean.Parser.Term.optConfig`, possibly wrapped\nin null nodes.\n\nWhen `logExceptions` is true, it uses the current `errToSorry` state to decide whether or not to\nrecover by logging errors and skipping invalid options.\n\nThe command will transitively derive any necessary `ConfigEval.EvalTerm`/`ConfigEval.EvalExpr`\ninstances to support evaluation of configuration options for structure fields.\nThese instances will be `private local`.\n\nSee `ConfigEval.defEvalConfigItemCmd` for further documentation.\n\nSee also `declare_core_config_elab`, `declare_config_elab`, and `declare_command_config_elab`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareTermConfigElab","kind":"def","line":116,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareTermConfigElab","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L116-L138"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareCoreConfigElab\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">declareCoreConfigElab</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`declare_core_config_elab f struct binders* [where ...]` defines a configuration elaborator\n```lean\nf binders* (cfg : Syntax) (init : struct := {}) (logExceptions : Bool := false) : CoreM struct\n```\nthat evaluates the `cfg` configuration items to update `init`.\nAcceptable configuration syntax is documented in `Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.foldConfigM`,\nwhich includes anything that looks like `Lean.Parser.Term.optConfig`, possibly wrapped\nin null nodes.\n\nThe command will transitively derive any necessary `ConfigEval.EvalTerm`/`ConfigEval.EvalExpr`\ninstances to support evaluation of configuration options for structure fields.\nThese instances will be `private local`.\n\nSee `ConfigEval.defEvalConfigItemCmd` for further documentation.\n\nSee also `declare_term_config_elab`, `declare_config_elab`, and `declare_command_config_elab`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareCoreConfigElab","kind":"def","line":95,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.declareCoreConfigElab","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L95-L114"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.defEvalConfigItemCmd\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">defEvalConfigItemCmd</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`def_eval_config_item f binders* for struct` defines a `ConfigEval.EvalConfigItem struct` structure named `f`\nparameterized by the given binders. This structure contains a setter for updating a configuration\nobject of type `struct`.\n\nThe command will transitively derive any necessary `ConfigEval.EvalTerm`/`ConfigEval.EvalExpr`\ninstances to support evaluation of configuration options for structure fields.\nThe syntax supports `public`/`private` modifiers. It also supports `scoped`/`local`, which apply\nto any derived instances.\n\nThe `EvalConfigItem struct` structure can be customized with a `where` clause.\nThe possible items of the `where` clause are:\n- `omit f1, f2, f3` disables generating setters for fields `f1`, `f2`, and `f3` of `struct`\n- `option key := fun cfg item => ...` adds a configuration option named `key` with the given\nexpression as its handler. The handler is only called when the key is an exact match.\nThe provided value is in `item.value`. Such a handler implies `omit key`.\n- `option key* := fun cfg item => ...` adds configuration options with `key` as a proper prefix.\nThe most-specific `*` handler is called if no handlers for exact matches apply.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.defEvalConfigItemCmd","kind":"def","line":73,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.defEvalConfigItemCmd","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L73-L93"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntries\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">configEntries</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntries","kind":"def","line":71,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntries","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L71-L71"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntry\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">configEntry</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntry","kind":"def","line":70,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntry","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L70-L70"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandler\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">configEntryHandler</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`option key := fun cfg item => ...` adds a configuration option named `key` with the given\nexpression as its handler. The handler is only called when the key is an exact match.\nThe provided value is in `item.value`. Such a handler implies `omit key`.\n\n`option key.* := fun cfg item => ...` adds configuration options with `key` as a proper prefix.\nThe most-specific `*` handler is called if no handlers for exact matches apply.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandler","kind":"def","line":61,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandler","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L61-L69"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKey\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">configEntryHandlerKey</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"- `key` matches a specific key\n- `key.*` matches any keys for which `key` is a proper prefix\n- `*` matches all keys\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKey","kind":"def","line":55,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKey","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L55-L60"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKeyWildcard\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">configEntryHandlerKeyWildcard</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKeyWildcard","kind":"def","line":54,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKeyWildcard","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L54-L54"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKeyPrefix\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">configEntryHandlerKeyPrefix</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKeyPrefix","kind":"def","line":53,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryHandlerKeyPrefix","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L53-L53"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryOmit\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">configEntryOmit</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`omit f1, f2, f3` disables generating setters for fields `f1`, `f2`, and `f3`\nof the structure. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryOmit","kind":"def","line":50,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.configEntryOmit","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L50-L52"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.deriveEvalExprUsingMeta\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">deriveEvalExprUsingMeta</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`derive_eval_expr_instance_using_meta_eval type` defines a `ConfigItem.EvalExpr type` instance\nusing `Meta.evalExpr'` to evaluate expressions. This sort of item evaluator is a reasonable\nbackup strategy for infrequently used configuration options, if term- or expression-based\nevaluation does not work and the cost of compilation is acceptible.\n\nThis should be avoided in core Lean due to the difficulties it creates for bootstrapping.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.deriveEvalExprUsingMeta","kind":"def","line":40,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.deriveEvalExprUsingMeta","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L40-L48"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalTermExprInstances\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">ensureEvalTermExprInstances</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`ensure_eval_term_expr_instances t` is a macro for running both `ensure_eval_term_instance t`\nand `ensure_eval_expr_instance t`, which ensurs there are `ConfigItem.EvalTerm t` and\n`ConfigItem.EvalExpr t` instances by deriving one or more instances if it needs to.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalTermExprInstances","kind":"def","line":33,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalTermExprInstances","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L33-L38"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalExprInstance\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">ensureEvalExprInstance</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`ensure_eval_expr_instance t` ensures there is a `ConfigItem.EvalExpr t` instance by\nderiving one or more instances if it needs to.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalExprInstance","kind":"def","line":27,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalExprInstance","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L27-L31"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalTermInstance\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">ensureEvalTermInstance</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`ensure_eval_term_instance t` ensures there is a `ConfigItem.EvalTerm t` instance by\nderiving one or more instances if it needs to.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalTermInstance","kind":"def","line":21,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.ensureEvalTermInstance","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Commands.lean#L21-L25"}}],"imports":["Init.Notation"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.Commands"}